OL,3,CMiners march on Downing Street against
OL,4,C'daylight robbery' in pension row
OL,6,FThey argue that it is unfair that the
OL,7,Fgovernment takes 50 per cent of all
OL,8,Fsurplus money generated by the
OL,9,FMineworkers Pension Scheme under a
OL,10,Fguarantee introduced in 1994, when
OL,11,FBritish Coal was privatised.
OL,13,FSince then, the guarantee has
OL,14,Fgenerated around #5 billion for the
OL,15,Fgovernment and campaigners say that if
OL,16,Fcurrent trends continue, the
OL,17,Fgovernment could take another #1
OL,18,Fbillion over the next decade.
