OL,3,CMiners march on Downing Street against
OL,4,C'daylight robbery' in pension row
OL,6,FBert Moncur, who worked at Murton
OL,7,FColliery in County Durham, led the
OL,8,Fmarch in the capital. He said: "They
OL,9,Ftook away death funds and everything
OL,10,Felse. Any penny they can take off the
OL,11,Fminers, they do it.
OL,13,F"It's been an absolute disgrace. It's
OL,14,Fdaylight robbery. No government should
OL,15,Fbe robbing its people, full stop. They
OL,16,Fdidn't put a penny in. They keep
OL,17,Fsaying they're protecting the
OL,18,Ftaxpayer. How are the taxpayers being
OL,19,Fprotected if they didn't make a penny
OL,20,Fout of it?
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/9
