OL,3,CMiners march on Downing Street against
OL,4,C'daylight robbery' in pension row
OL,6,FThe former miners claim that since
OL,7,F1994, successive governments, both
OL,8,FLabour and Conservative, have let the
OL,9,Fmining community down - particularly
OL,10,Fthe widows of former mineworkers, who
OL,11,Fonly receive around #8 to #10 per week.
OL,13,FIn 2021, a parliamentary select
OL,14,Fcommittee by paying out around #1.2
OL,15,Fbillion to top up the pensions of
OL,16,Fformer mineworkers.
