OL,3,CMiners march on Downing Street against
OL,4,C'daylight robbery' in pension row
OL,6,FAt the time, the Business, Energy and
OL,7,FIndustrial Strategy Committee said
OL,8,Fthat given the "vast sums" paid from
OL,9,Fthe scheme to the government, it was
OL,10,F"unconscionable" that miners were
OL,11,Fstruggling.
OL,13,FGrahame Morris MP, who represents
OL,14,FEasington, said: "This is the miners'
OL,15,Fmoney. The government and British
OL,16,FCoal, the NCB, have made no
OL,17,Fcontribution to that fund for almost
OL,18,Ffifty years, ten years before the
OL,19,Fstrike. I think that's an unreasonable
OL,20,Fsum to take out.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/9
