OL,3,CMiners march on Downing Street against
OL,4,C'daylight robbery' in pension row
OL,6,F"Even in the worst of times
OL,7,Feconomically, the global crash of
OL,8,F2009, the government were never asked
OL,9,Fto contribute to underwrite the scheme.
OL,11,F"So unless there was some financial
OL,12,Fcommitment or cost to the government,
OL,13,FI don't think there's a strong moral
OL,14,For legal case for them to be taking
OL,15,Fbillions of pounds out of the scheme.
OL,16,FThat could benefit some of the poorest
OL,17,Fpeople. A widow's pension is very
OL,18,Fmodest, some as low as #8 per week.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/9
